1040
01:26:59,100 --> 01:27:04,100
If you want to make a fun game, you're often breaking the laws of physics.

1041
01:27:04,100 --> 01:27:09,100
You have superpowers and magic and things like that.

1042
01:27:09,100 --> 01:27:13,100
A game developer has to recoup their investment,

1043
01:27:13,100 --> 01:27:17,100
which means they need to be able to sell their game to many gamers,

1044
01:27:17,100 --> 01:27:22,100
which means it has to run on many types of computers and small computers.

1045
01:27:22,100 --> 01:27:27,100
Game engines are designed to run on phones, on consoles,

1046
01:27:27,100 --> 01:27:33,100
on maybe a high-end gaming PC, but they're really optimized

1047
01:27:33,100 --> 01:27:38,100
for running on the lowest common denominator kind of system.

1048
01:27:38,100 --> 01:27:41,100
And what you'll give up when you're going to make your game run

1049
01:27:41,100 --> 01:27:46,100
on as many devices as possible is physical accuracy and fidelity.

1050
01:27:46,100 --> 01:27:49,100
You'll reduce the detail level of the worlds.

1051
01:27:49,100 --> 01:27:54,100
